text.text:
It's easy to spend an hour or more at the Purrista Cat Cafe and enjoy the cats, work quietly, and get some nice coffee or snack while you wait.

The location takes up two building spaces, one side for the coffee cafe and the other as a home for the cats. The cats are all up for adoption, and Purrista does a great job of ensuring cats are happy, calm, and relaxed in the cafe while they're being pet.

Enjoy the atmosphere and be calm. They offer shoe covers, as they don't allow shoes in the same room as the cats, and also give plenty of sanitizer wipes and lint rollers to clean up afterwards.

Definitely recommend!

First time there and it was everything I dreamed it would be!!
The cafe was adorable and the drinks were fantastic. I didn‚Äôt try any pastries due to an allergy üò´ but they looked delicious.
The cat room was spacious and the cats all seem very happy and comfortable there. It was easy to interact with them.
The employees were all very nice, informative and friendly.

This place will be my first stop if I'm ever back in Erie! I loved the setup of a regular cafe on one side, which opens early morning, and a cat area on the other (opens at 11). I got some work done, had a nice cup of tea in one of their cute mugs, then went to the cat side when it opened. Immediately one of the younger cats attached himself to me and slept on my lap and shoulders while I finished my work. The other cats were so cute too! Great vibes, very clean (you take your shoes off for the cat area so wear socks). Every other cat cafe I've been to just kinda pours coffee from a pot or a cup of juice into a paper cup lol, and no food. By separating the cafe from the cat area, Purrista stands as a legitimately good coffee shop on its own!

cafes.name: Purrfect Mugs Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1325 N River St Suite 102A, Hilldale, PA 18702, USA

text.text: Workers were so sweet and so were the kitties! Reasonable pricing, adorable gift shop and yummy coffee!! So many cats to pet and play with, and most were up for adoption!! :)

This is a good place with good drinks. I got a blue raspberry Italian soda which in my opinion was pretty good, There are 14 cats as of 1/13/24 and some love to sleep and some are playful. One of the cats named Sassy is 100% named correctly because he is sassy! It can be busy with a wait if you walk-in without a reservation but it's worth the wait. I recommend that you make a reservation if you have a particular time you want to go at.
Always a great experience. Drinks are fun, staff is always friendly. The concept to help homeless kitties find furever homes is great.

Doylestown.name: MeWow Cat Cafe
Doylestown.address: 3617 Old Easton Rd, Doylestown, PA 18902, USA

text.text:
I happen to be googling something else. Another brick and mortar business but this caught my eye and was surprised there was a cat cafe nearby us!!

This is unusual for me to give 4 stars.

I took one less star because they don‚Äôt want any kids under 5. Their rule and I had leave my 3 year old son at home rather than enjoying this cat cafe experience with his big brother.

Place is kept clean. Friendly, one in particular who was very nice.

I didn‚Äôt catch their names as they were not wearing one

Tea, coffee or any snacks are not part of the ticket when you get into their kitty coral

Would i come back again‚Ä¶? Most likely not

Otherwise, the cat experience satisfied my son to play with their cats for 25 minutes.

It is highly recommended to book your cat experience through their website. It does have a fee to book it and they would charge credit card processing fee if you were to purchase something in store.

We only book the 25 minutes and here is what I‚Äôve paid for

It‚Äôs $10 per adult
$7 for children 5-12 year old

This was our first time here, and I LOVED it!! Such a cute little place, and the employees were very nice! The cats were ADORABLE, I wanted to take them home! But alas, I already have 4 üòî (although what's one more?). All the stuff they had to buy was perfect for cats and cat lovers alike, and the treats and drinks were delicious! I can't wait to come back ü•∞üíï

Always love visiting the kittens and cats!!  Everyone who works there are so incredible and so sweet w. All the cats!!! I help out with Kitty Junction who of the rescues there and mewow cafe is THE best place to visit!!! I stopped over today in fact and loved snuggling with thr kittens!!

Had the best time with the cats here at Whiskers! The owners/workers are gems of people who are just so kind and want you to be comfortable and meet all the babies. They are dedicated to the cats in their care and are quite laid back.
The kitten room was fun but was hard to enjoy due to the smell. The room does not get circulation so there is a very overwhelming litter smell. That can probably be aided with air purifiers and litter deodorizer. Overall I enjoyed my visit, will likely be back, and will be recommending to others!

The owner is incredibly sweet, with stories about each cat that shows she is invested in the future of them all. Sweeter than her are the cats themselves! They are very friendly to humans. If you're ever looking to adopt a cat, I would highly recommend this place

Tim and Lina are so sweet!! They introduced us to each cat and kitten and offered comfort & beverages. They made the cafe feel like a familiar home. All the cats were so sweet and adorable. Definitely a place to visit to de-stress if you love cats.

cafes.name: Le Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 2713 W Girard Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19130, USA

text.text:
Well, this was a first for me. My daughter loves cats, so we went to a cat cafe. A very interesting place, they bring in stray cats off the streets and give them a place to stay, hoping to be adopted. They are cleaned, tested, vaccinated, and spayed/neutered.
The cafe looks like a playground for cats, with toys and platforms all over for the cats to entertain themselves.
The cafe also offers free coffee/tea, hot cocoa and other drinks to enjoy while you keep the cats company.
All the cats are up for adoption or to foster. In 2024 alone, they had gotten over 350 cats adopted! It was a fun time, especially watching my daughter‚Äôs heart melt while the 10+ cats in this place scurried around and played!

had a nice time at this cafe. so many cats with different personalities, it was nice to get to know some of them a bit. the workers knew a lot about each cat and were really helpful in their explanation. they were also really friendly which is always a plus. i just came for the vibes, though i would potentially be open to adopting a cat in the right timing. i do wish they had non-caffeinated tea which was the only down side for me. will likely return. üíó

This place goes above and beyond to help find loving homes for cats. I adopted a cat from there in 2019 and renamed him Alamo. All the cats in the cafe are available for adoption and even if someone is not looking to adopt, they can come and play with cats while sipping coffee. Bree, one of the ladies that works there was so friendly and told us about all the cats; their names and personalities. She also listened while I told her about my cat. This place is amazing!

Such a wonderful place. Great coffee and treats, and best of all, you get to cuddle with cats. All the cats are up for adoption too, so if you're looking for a new furry friend, stop by. The owner is very friendly and gave us some good insights into the town.

My husband, daughter and I visited Dexter's to visit with cats.  Brittney is extremely friendly and told us about each cat in the room.  We loved meeting all of the cats and learning their stories.  We submitted an application for Coconut before we left and are hoping to adopt him.  We will definately be back to visit, have a coffee and play with the cats in the future!  It's a great way to spend some time in the afternoon, help cats and enjoy a tasty drink!

Absolutely wonderful! Company of cats and some really friendly folks while sipping on an espresso drink and munching on a pastery.
Plenty of seating in the main lobby as well as the cat room.  Parking in the back or on the street.
a minimal fee based in time to spend with the cats, proceeds go to assist in caring and finding homes for the darling felines. Gift cards are available, a small section of cat themed items.

Drinks are Fantabulous, staff is great, pasteries delectable and the cats are just swell.

Family brunch at a small cafe in Devon. I have to admit I was kind of freaked out when we arrived and they had a number of cats in crates near the front door. But I have come to learn that this is a non-profit operation where all the proceeds benefit the needs of homeless, abandoned, injured and sick cats and kittens.  Wow! They were very accommodating to us when we had to keep changing our reservation. Kudos to them!!!  The actual food was just okay.  My home fries were burned.  My French toast was mildly tasty.  The creamed chipped beef had a very odd flavor (too eggy or too much uncooked flour).  Nothing was extraordinary, but I applaud the cause.

Phenomenal! The food was incredible. Had the bacon, tomato and grilled cheese sandwich. Service was very accommodating because two minutes after we were sat we found out our next appointment moved up and they quickly changed our order to- go and had us on our way. And of course the cats were adorable.

Excellent service: attentive, thorough, and accommodating with recommendations and options. By far the best chip beef I‚Äôve been served, the custom omelette was perfect and the sourdough toast it came with was fresh, flavorful and perfectly toasted. If you like scrapple, they cook it to absolute perfection. Pan seared, not deep fried, as it should be. üòÆ‚Äçüí®ü§å
10/10 would recommend and come back!!

cafes.name: Coal Cats Cafe
cafes.address: 209 W Broad St, Tamaqua, PA 18252, USA

text.text:
We were walking by and wanted to grab a cup of coffee. We came in and ended up getting an hour of cat-time ($10/hr) and some lattes.

The owner was very friendly and knowledgeable. They gave around 10 cats that they get from the rescue and assist in getting the cats adopted/ socialized (and you get cat time). Their cat area is clean with lots of nooks and crannies for the cats. They can fit ~8 people so if you want cat time be sure to book ahead.

The coffee was solid and the gift shop area was cute. Next time I'm in tamaqua I'd stop by for the coffee (and the cats are a plus too)!

I loved playing with the kitties and getting to know them. It's a great way to consider adoption or even just to have some kitty play time. The owner was super nice and have lots of information to help get to know them. Worth the drive. There is coffee, soda and some snacks for those who show up starving and kitty themed gifts.

The trip I took here for my birthday was one of the best experiences I could ask for. From the staff who cares so much about the cats and have endless knowledge of all of them, the coffee being quite tasty and the selection of unique gifts. This place was beyond my expectations. I highly suggest this as a fun little trip!

cafes.name: Kitt's Caf√© & Gandalf's Garden
cafes.address: 8520 Allentown Pike Ste 13 & 14, Blandon, PA 19510, USA

text.text:
This cat cafe is a must-visit! The space is bright, clean and spacious, filled with charming cat-themed merchandise and interesting houseplants. The coffee shop is great, offering delicious baked goods and pastries ‚Äì especially their cinnamon rolls, which are by far the best I've ever had! Order one and thank me later!

The real stars of the cafe are the adorable kittens and cats! There were so many sweet and playful adoptable cats roaming around, looking for cuddles and playtime. The staff were incredibly friendly and knowledgeable about each cat, and the adoption process is done on site.

Whether you're a cat lover, a coffee enthusiast, or simply looking for a unique and heartwarming experience, this cafe is for you!

I‚Äôll be back with my laptop to work remotely in the cat room!  Totally worth the cost of entry to have the purrrfect remote working companions!

me and my friend went to this cat cafe, the closet one to reading. this is the best place ever.

for food i ordered chicken bacon ranch wrap, a HUGE cinnamon roll, and the tiramisu iced coffee.
I'm NOT overexaggerating, that food was AMAZING. Everything was a 10/10. The wrap, chicken was cooked perfectly, bacon was good and crisp, ranch tasted so good, all of it combined was heaven. The cinnamon roll was HUGE, its a MOUTAIN roll, it's so different than store brought, the icing is so different from store brought but its the best cinnamon roll icing i ever tasted, let alone the BEST cinnamon roll I've tasted in my whole 17 years. It's the most softest, tastiest, mouth watering cinnamon roll you'll EVER come across. and then the tiramisu iced coffee, OH MY GOD. i never taste anything like that, its so unique and genius. i just love it. no words.
my friend only got the mini breakfast pizza bacon egg and cheddar. i tasted it, THE BREAD IS SUPER SOFT, YOU NEED TO TRY. TRY IT TRY IT TRY IT TRY ITT. ITS SO GOOD SOFT AND SMELLS GOOD.

I HIGHLY RECCOMEND TRYING THAT WRAP AND CINNAMANROLL. also if they have that s'more brownie TRY IT, i sadly wasn't able to today but soon.

now for the cats.
$8 per person for 30 minutes.
and i THINK $12 for 60 minutes per person.
there's hand sanitizer and lint rollers already, there's a door to the cat room and then a gate. there's cat toys so you can play with them. i heard if you go early most of the cats are up (I'm not positive) I went around 3:30PM.
the big chunky black cat is ace, I LOOVE HIM. HE WOKE UP FORM HIS SLUMBER AND INSANTLY CAME TO ME. THE WHITE ONE was so cute, look at the pink paws. literally so adorable. theres a kitten too, SO MANY CATSS.

the atsmposphere was nice, I wasn't able to get pictures because I was least focus on that but its a nice quiet cafe, i feel like i can work on my school assignments there peacefully. they have music but its low, and the staff was friendly.

overall i REALLY recommend this place.

If you love Cats, Coffee, and Plants, this is a fun place to visit. Lots of cats to just hang out with and drink your coffee/latte/tea. They have a small selection of nice looking house plants... including cat grass.

cafes.name: Cattfeinated Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 159 E Otterman St, Greensburg, PA 15601, USA

text.text: If your a cat lover and enjoy coffee then this is the place for you.  They are currently housing between 25-30 cats.  They have two rooms for visits- the kitten room and the adult cat room.  The cafe is separate from the cats and they serve a full range of hot, iced and frozen coffees.  The entire place is immaculately clean.  They also have a small section to purchase gifts and miscellaneous items.  To visit the cats there is a small fee from $5.00 a person for 15 minutes to $10.00 for 30 minutes.  They do take reservations for visits and I can imagine that is necessary at times.  You must also remove your shoes and sanitize your hands before entering.  Picking up the cats is not allowed and sleeping cats are not to be disturbed.  You can pet and play with the cats if they decide you are worthy lol.  They do a great service for unwanted cats by fostering them until homes can be found.  Had a great time and the money spent was for a great cause.

We came here for date night and had an amazing time. The staff was friendly and they have so many amazing cats for adoption. My favorite kitten was Piper. We aren‚Äôt ready to adopt but will come back next time we want to see some kitties!

We had such a great time here! The coffees were amazing and the prices were very reasonable. We spent 30 minutes with the cats and they were so sweet and fun to hang out with. The whole place was clean. Will definitely be back!

cafes.name: Craig‚Äôs Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 11 Riverside Dr, Spring City, PA 19475, USA

text.text: Absolutely the most precious little cafe with such a great cause! They sell coffee, treats & little trinkets where % of proceeds go to rescuing cats lives. Super friendly staff (small business ran by a mother and her two daughters); Cafe and cat area were both very clean, all kittens are up for adoption which is ran through a legit rescue that they partnered up with. Entry fee is $5 (with age restrictions for children & ONLY adults can pick the kittens up - children are not allowed‚Ä¶which I greatly RESPECT them for having these rules in place for the kittens safety). Overall, it was such a cute/pleasant experience and I can‚Äôt wait to bring my cat lover family & friends. Kudos
I can't get enough of this place! It‚Äôs my go-to whenever I need a mood boost or just want to relax. The cats are so friendly and absolutely adorable, making it impossible not to smile! :)

Stopped by on a Sunday afternoon.  We are not newbies to this concept as we are regulars at Cats in Bloom in Bloomsburg PA.

The good:
Cats are clearly well cared for.
The room was the appropriate size for the number of cats.
Cats had access to clean water and food.
Cats had plenty of toys and some safe spaces if they didn‚Äôt want to socialize.

The bad:
I 1000% disagree with the age policy (kids of all ages are allowed).  There were 3 kids there when we arrived (all clearly no more than age 7-8).  Two of them were relentlessly following cats around that clearly didn‚Äôt want to socialize with them.  One cat ‚Äúwarned‚Äù one of the kids multiple times but she didn‚Äôt stop.  Literally all of the cats but 1-2 were in a hiding spot.  Then a mom with FOUR kids walked in (age range was probably 5-10). That‚Äôs when we left.  I just couldn‚Äôt watch these kids stressing the cats out any longer.  Also - this was not a large room and there were now 8 adults and 7 kids in there.

My opinion may not be popular but I dont believe the owner‚Äôs intent is for this to be a petting zoo when it‚Äôs too cold for your kids to go outside.  And I realize an age policy may reduce the number of visitors - I‚Äôd happily spend more on admission to see these cats not have to deal with the stress of young children.

I also think there should be a reservation system or a time limit or some way to cut down on the number of people in that room at one time.  At least at high traffic times.

I really love this concept but there needs to be an age policy and you need more space.  Personally I would get rid of the cafe side and make the whole thing cat visitation.

cafes.name: Cat Nook Cafe
cafes.address: 18 W Winona Ave, Norwood, PA 19074, USA

text.text: The cats are so cute and friendly! The cafe is decorated so well and cute! The staff is friendly and very helpful. The merch is worth buying and the cafe is in a great area. Definitely a chill place to forget everything when you're petting cats for an hour! We'll be visiting again.

The Cat Nook Cafe in Norwood is a haven for cat lovers. For just $10 an hour, you can relax and enjoy the company of  10-12 adorable, adoptable cats! The fee goes directly to supporting the organization and the care of these furry friends.

The staff are incredibly friendly and clearly passionate about their feline residents. They're happy to share information about each cat's personality and care, which adds a personal touch.  While the cat area is cozy, it's a clean and comfortable space with plenty of seating for around 6 people.  There are even a few toys available so you can engage and play with the cats!

What's even better is that all the kitties are available for adoption.  They've partnered with a local rescue, giving these furry friends a chance to find their forever homes.

It's the perfect spot to unwind and de-stress with some feline company.  Parking is easy, too, with spots available along the side of the road and a parking area across the street. Highly recommend a visit!

Cute place! Small cafe area where you can buy coffee, tea, and snacks. Cat lounge had around 10 kitties, all very friendly. Less of a cafe; you come for the cats! It was so nice to just hang out and play with them. There are lots of toys and beds for the cats. Couches for the people. They had music on for a nice ambiance. There was a family there at the same time as me, but I didn't mind sharing time with them. I would love to come back soon!

cafes.name: Treetops Kitty Cafe - Cat Adoption and Visitation Center
cafes.address: 305 W State St, Kennett Square, PA 19348, USA

text.text: Wish I could take all the kitties home! It‚Äôs such a lovely space and the adoptable cats are happy and well-cared for. Was happy to support them with the entry fee and purchasing some merch. Come find your next fur-friend here!

We went to cat Bingo last night and it was really fun.  They had a nice set of prizes and the bingo was fun but the best part was all the cat shenanigans going on the entire time.  That‚Äôs a group of super lucky kitties to have Treetop as their temporary home.

I have visited the cafe over 3 times and each time is a relaxing and enjoyable experience with the cats. The newest interior is gorgeous and you can tell the cats have lots of stimulating toys and places to climb, run and sleep. I actually adopted my first cat from Treetops and they helped me with all my anxious cat questions and followed up with me multiple times after adoption. My kitty was previously feral and they were honest with me about her entire situation and history. She is an anxious girl but so am I and we are truly peas in a pod. We are constantly with each other at home and I am so so lucky to have this angel of a kitty. Thank you Treetops!! I recommend them 100%

Such a wonderful cat cafe! Relaxed environment, wonderful owner, and I love that they offer other little trinkets and toys for cats. Adopted Edgar (formerly Seye) from here, and I‚Äôm forever grateful for them giving me the opportunity to meet all of the cats, and eventually my best friend!

This is the best cat room I have ever been to. The staff are so friendly and really knowledgeable about the cats they have there. It is super clean and the cats are taken excellent care of.
Adopting through them and their partner rescue is a very easy and pleasant process. I cannot say enough good things. They answered all of my questions and made the process super seamless. I have never had a cat adoption go so smoothly.
You can tell that the staff here and at the partner rescue really love what they, and they do it really well.
One of the best places to go in Pittsburgh!

Livy is a gem of a human being and takes such good care of these cats. She has helped literally hundreds of cats find furrever homes. If you‚Äôre not in the market to adopt but you need a fuzzy snuggle fix, this is the place to go! Love love LOVE this place!

cafes.name: Cats in Bloom - Bloomsburg Cat Cafe‚Äô
cafes.address: 102 W Main St, Bloomsburg, PA 17815, USA

text.text: My daughter wanted to visit here for her birthday. I had never been there before, but she has. It's $5 per person to visit and your visit is about an hour long. The young cats and kittens are the most playful and they have a variety of toys provided, including a laser. My daughter had an absolute blast playing with all of them. While we are not looking to adopt any right now, I know where to go when we are.

Such an awesome place to keep cats free roaming and out of cages while waiting for their new homes. It‚Äôs very inexpensive $5 for an entire hour! There are kittens in a kitten room and adult cats in the main room. They accept donations of cat toys, beds and anything kitty! I plan to bring some gently used toys that my girls don‚Äôt play with anymore. I have two cats of my own but this is a nice way to get my kitty ‚Äúfix‚Äù without adding more to my home.

This place is absolutely wonderful. It‚Äôs super super clean, friendly and just an influx of kitty cat love.
My partner and I just swung in for a quick lunch break and I just fell in love with Stevie (though, I immediately started saying, ‚Äúoh, Stephen, you sweet little man cat‚Äù).
Not only is it a lovely place to indulge oneself in ‚Äòwarm fuzzies‚Äô, but it‚Äôs a nonprofit/volunteer organization which makes me feel even warmer inside.
A+++, guys!

Mount Laurel Township.name: Four Green Cats Cafe
Mount Laurel Township.address: 118 Creek Rd, Mt Laurel Township, NJ 08054, USA

text.text:
Four Green Cats Cafe - WORTH the wait!

Four Green Cats Caf√© is an absolute gem - a fabulous coffee shop specializing in Czech & European-inspired sweets and savories that are as delightful - unique. My Caramel Latte was perfectly craft, but my latte, amazing as it was, couldn‚Äôt compete with the star of the show: a freshly baked, hot-out-of-the-oven savory doughnut.

This isn‚Äôt your average savory doughnut. It‚Äôs a sweet and savory pastry stuffed with tangy sauerkraut, a slice of sausage, cherry tomato, a sweet pickle slice, and fresh greens. With every bite, my taste buds were intrigued and delighted. The balance of flavors had me wanting to lick my plate!  I didn't : )

The caf√© is cozy and inviting, and the ‚ÄúCats‚Äù (slang for pretty girls and referring to the owner & her family) know their pastries! I managed to resist the German bread pudding and other indulgent sweets, they looked incredible !

Be sure to check out the caf√©‚Äôs history online - there is a wonderful article worth reading. The owner and her family (Cats) have truly created a landmark that‚Äôs just slightly off the beaten path, both physically and in its distinctive cuisine.

SO WHY did I say it was worth the wait?  During the hustling months, the line can be quite long, BUT don't let that deter you!  The wait is worth it for both coffee and authentically created food.  Don‚Äôt miss it‚Äîvisit Four Green Cats Caf√© soon!

A very comfy cafe with comfortable seats and desserts. It is connected to an antique shop which is also good to look around. My wife was bold enough to try Jade Cloud (Jade from Green tea and cloud from milk) which I‚Äôd avoid next visit. Coffee was however good and mild.
Love this place! Their pastries are all phenomenal. We love the Bread pudding, brioche and the donuts. Coffee drinks are great too and staff is always friendly.

Great place to stop by to relax with some friendly cats and kittens. The space is very clean and the staff are very accommodating and friendly. There‚Äôs only a small charge to enter that goes to towards their rescue/housing costs, and outside food/drinks are allowed. Come through and make some feline friends! Better yet, bring one into your home!

Been here twice now and it's such a joy to play with and pet the kitties.  They're so adorable and I love watching them make the Cafe their own space.  There are plenty of cats there and it's so awesome that they're all adoptable!  I only wish I lived closer so I could walk there every day!

Cats there are. Cafe there is not. Perhaps I was not the only one hoping for a cup of coffee or tea or snack while watching and interacting with cats. The owners were nice but watching capacity they would encourage you to leave if you spend too much time lingering and others were waiting. It was fun but would have been nicer if there was an actual caf√© there.

cafes.name: The Cats Meow
cafes.address: 215 S Charlotte St, Manheim, PA 17545, USA

text.text:
We've come to this restaurant many times o er the last few years and it NEVER disappoints! Also great food, great staff and great atmosphere. Such a neat building and roaring 20's decor! We will be back! 10/10 recommend!

Food we got: Ceasar Salad (came with grilled chicken), Meatball appetizer, Chicken Fingers and Braided Pretzel.

An amazing place to visit and dine in! It‚Äôs a combination of a friendly family restaurant and a 1920s bourgeoisie speakeasy. The drinks are crafted in a 1920s style and taste like nothing you‚Äôve ever tried before. I personally recommend the gin cocktail. The food is authentic, reminiscent of what people would have eaten in the 1920s‚Äîsimple and original, without any of the fancy additives developed in recent times to manipulate taste buds. It‚Äôs genuinely good. I would definitely come back to try more unique drinks and dishes. The staff is attentive and always goes above and beyond to make your experience special. And there's more: Karaoke Saturdays start at 9 p.m.!

First time here - love the atmosphere and the food! Enjoyed the rum runner from the drink menu. The server was friendly, fast, and attentive. Free parking in the lot across the street. Great place, would visit again.
